SUMMARY—Revises provisions governing grants made by the
State. (BDR 31-433)
FISCAL NOTE: Effect on Local Government: No.
Effect on the State: Yes.
~
EXPLANATION – Matter in bolded italics is new; matter between brackets [omitted material] is material to be omitted.
AN ACT relating to grants; declaring the policy of this State to
make payments under a grant agreement within a certain
period of time; imposing interest on amounts due under a
written grant agreement which are not timely paid after
the receipt of a proper invoice; requiring State entities that
make grants to take certain actions upon receipt of an
invoice; authorizing use of media other than original
paper documents to process grant payments; and
providing other matters properly relating thereto.
Legislative Counsel’s Digest:
1 This bill enacts requirements governing payments by State agencies to certain
2 nonprofit organizations that receive grants from those agencies and are reimbursed
3 by State agencies for services or other performance under a grant agreement.
4 Section 3 of this bill defines the term “grant” to establish the types of financial
5 assistance to which these requirements apply. Section 6 of this bill establishes that
6 the requirements of this bill do not apply to the Judicial Branch or Legislative
7 Branch of State Government, the Nevada System of Higher Education or any
8 institution within the System, or certain grants that support the State Public Works
9 Division of the Department of Administration in carrying out a program of capital
10 improvements. Section 10 of this bill excludes from the requirements of this bill
11 payments under grants which are executed, renewed or extended before July 1,
12 2025.
13 Section 7 of this bill declares that it is the policy of this State to complete all
14 processing and authorizations required by law to make a payment, as set forth in
