1 (a) Direct government cash assistance to a person;
2 (b) A subsidy;
3 (c) A loan;
4 (d) A loan guarantee;
5 (e) Insurance; or
6 (f) State funding that is required annually and is calculated
7 through a formula set in statute.
8 Sec. 4. “Payment” includes all processing and authorization
9 required by law from the State Board of Examiners, the Director
10 of the Office of Finance and the State Controller.
11 Sec. 5. “Proper invoice” means a bill, a written document or
12 an electronic transmission readable by the State grant-making
13 entity, provided by a grant recipient, that:
14 1. Requests an amount that is due and payable by law under
15 a written grant agreement; and
16 2. Includes:
17 (a) The federal employer identification number or social
18 security number of the grant recipient;
19 (b) Sufficient information to identify the grant agreement; and
20 (c) Any additional documentation the grant agreement
21 requires.
22 Sec. 6. The provisions of sections 2 to 9, inclusive, of this act
23 do not apply to:
24 1. The Legislative Department or Judicial Department of
25 State Government;
26 2. The Nevada System of Higher Education or any institution
27 of the Nevada System of Higher Education; or
28 3. Grants funded from general obligation bond proceeds or
29 from an appropriation made to the State Public Works Division of
30 the Department of Administration to support the Division in
31 carrying out a program of capital improvements.
32 Sec. 7. The Legislature declares that it is the policy of this
33 State to make a payment under a grant agreement within 37 days
34 after the later of:
35 1. The date on which the payment becomes due under the
36 grant agreement; or
37 2. The date on which the State grant-making entity receives a
38 proper invoice.
39 Sec. 8. 1. A State grant-making entity shall be liable for
40 interest at a rate of 9 percent per annum on any amount:
41 (a) That is due and payable by law under a written grant
42 agreement; and
43 (b) Which the State grant-making entity has failed, within 30
44 days after receipt of a proper invoice, to submit for payment in the
45 same manner as other claims against the State are paid.
