1 2. Interest under this section shall accrue beginning on the
2 38th day after the date on which the State grant-making entity
3 receives a proper invoice.
4 3. A State grant-making entity is not liable for interest
5 pursuant to this section:
6 (a) Unless the grant recipient submits an invoice for the
7 interest within 30 days after receiving payment for the amount on
8 which the interest accrued;
9 (b) If the State grant-making entity has initiated legal
10 proceedings to dispute the amount owed to the grant recipient;
11 (c) Accruing more than 1 year after the 31st day after the State
12 grant-making entity receives a proper invoice; or
13 (d) On an amount that represents unpaid interest.
14 4. Interest for which a State grant-making entity is liable
15 pursuant to this section:
16 (a) Must be paid from the operating budget of the State grant-
17 making entity; and
18 (b) May not be paid from funds appropriated to fund a grant.
19 5. For the purposes of determining the due date of a payment
20 and the date on which interest begins to accrue, an invoice is
21 deemed to be received:
22 (a) For invoices that are mailed, when a proper invoice is
23 received by the State grant-making entity, as of the date the State
24 grant-making entity annotates the invoice with the date and time
25 of receipt; or
26 (b) For invoices that are transmitted electronically, on the date
27 the transmission is received by the State grant-making entity or the
28 next business day if the transmission is received after 5 p.m.
29 Sec. 9. 1. Upon receipt of an invoice, a State grant-making
30 entity shall:
31 (a) Mark the invoice with the date the invoice was received;
32 and
33 (b) Review the invoice as soon as practicable to determine
34 whether the invoice is a proper invoice.
35 2. If the State grant-making entity determines that the
36 invoice:
37 (a) Is a proper invoice, the State grant-making entity shall
38 submit the invoice for payment in the same manner as other
39 claims against the State are paid.
40 (b) Is not a proper invoice, within 2 business days after making
41 such a determination, the State grant-making entity shall notify
42 the grant recipient of all defects that prevent the invoice from
43 being a proper invoice. It is the responsibility of the grant recipient
44 to submit a corrected invoice.
45 3. A State grant-making entity:
