1 (a) May use media that produce tangible recordings of
2 information to expedite the payment process, rather than delaying
3 the processes by requiring original paper documents; and
4 (b) Shall provide adequate safeguards and controls to ensure
5 the integrity of the data and to prevent duplicate processing.
6 4. Failure by a State grant-making entity to comply with the
7 procedural requirements of this section does not constitute a late
8 payment.
9 Sec. 10. The provisions of this act apply only to a grant, as
10 defined in section 3 of this act, which is executed, renewed or
11 extended on or after July 1, 2025.
12 Sec. 11. This act becomes effective on July 1, 2025.
